            <bug_when>2010-11-09 14:28:39 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Since the API Viewer is shipped &quot;pre-built&quot; in our release and linked on index.html, it is unfortunate that it cannot be opened via the file protocol. There is a not so slim chance that a would-be user opens index.html in Chrome and tries to follow the link to the API browser.

One work-around would be to add a notice to index.html, another to hide the link for Chrome users using the file protocol.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
